The Ministry  of Youth  and sports Development have unveiled the format for recently  revived  National Principal’s  cup competition for Secondary as the competition would run from the  states to the zones,  culminating in the finals billed for Abuja. Chairman  of the Organizing  committee  Dr. Ademola  Are stated: ” All is now set for the states, zonal and grand finale of the revived  National  Principal’s  Cup. The States finals would run from March 8th – 12th , with four teams per State, State champions will proceed to the zonal finals across the Six geopolitical zones from March 18th – 22nd  , while the national  final takes place from April 1st – 4th  in Abuja. “We are working round the clock to ensure a hitch-free competition. The NSSF, ANCOPSS & YSFON, are  working  with the Main organizing committee to  stage a seamless competition.” Meanwhile, President  of the Nigerian School Sports Federation  Mrs Olabisi Joseph said the NSSF have registered more than 132 schools  from 33 States  for the competition , adding there would be 22 events in athletics  as well as competition in football and table tennis. The Ceremonial  flag -of  the  competition   took place at the Agege Stadium in  Lagos on February 26th  with Igbobi  College, Lagos and Government  College, Kaduna playing a pulsating  1- 1 draw.